						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<p>It goes without saying that the <a
									href="https://www.androidauthority.com/apple-iphone-14-specs-price-availability-3213455/">iPhone</a>
								is the most widely recognized smartphone in the world. Apple ships nearly a quarter
								billion units each year and the company commands a market share of nearly 20%. With so
								many phones flying off shelves year after year, you may be wondering: where is the
								iPhone made, and how does the latest model reach customers so quickly each generation?
								Let’s break it down.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<h2>Before assembly: Where do iPhone components come from?</h2>
						</div>
