hority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-770w-433h.jpg 770w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-355w-200h.jpg 355w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-675w-380h.jpg 675w" alt="apple iphone 14 plus back standing" src="https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing.jpg"/></picture>
									<div class="-_-Ol -_-Gk">
										<div class="-_-8i">Ryan Haines / Android Authority</div>
									</div>
							</div>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<p>With singular components out of the way, who makes the iPhone before it reaches you?
								Factories in China once assembled every single iPhone, but that’s starting to change
								now.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="ad-banner -_-e in-article">
							<div></div>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-tg -_-ug"></div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<p>Still, most factories dedicated to assembling the iPhone remain in China. The largest
								one, operated by manufacturing partner Foxconn, is located in Zhengzhou and employs over
								300,000 workers. By many accounts, the complex <a
									href="https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/29/technology/apple-iphone-china-foxconn.html"
									target="_blank">resembles a mini city</a> more than a typical industrial site.
								That’s not surprising given that Foxconn reportedly assembles over half a million
								iPhones in a single day here. But that may not last forever as Apple looks to move some
								production to neighboring countries like India and Vietnam.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<q>Apple has diversified its iPhone production outside China of late, with India and Vietnam emerging as top choices.</q>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<p>Apple isn’t the only consumer electronics company that has diversified outside China of
								late. Samsung and Xiaomi have found great success in other Asian countries too. The <a
									href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Plus_One" target="_blank">China Plus
									One</a> strategy has become a popular business strategy as companies look to achieve
								lower operating costs and lower their reliance on a single region.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<p>Both Asian countries offer benefits to foreign investors looking to set up manufacturing
								facilities. They also offer geopolitical and economic stability — factors that severely
								affected Apple’s iPhone production in China. These bottlenecks even forced the company
								to put out a <a
									href="https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2022/11/update-on-supply-of-iphone-14-pro-and-iphone-14-pro-max/"
									target="_blank">press release</a> warning of longer wait times for deliveries.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="ad-banner -_-e in-article-related">
							<div></div>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<h3>Why does Apple assemble products in Vietnam?</h3>
							<p>Vietnam is strategically located for global shipping — the country is in close geographic
								proximity to Apple’s existing <a
									href="https://www.apple.com/supplier-responsibility/pdf/Apple-FY21-Supplier-List.pdf"
									target="_blank">supply chain footholds</a> such as China, Taiwan, Japan, and others.
								It also has free trade agreements with other East Asian countries and is a member of the
								Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN). Finally, Vietnam’s entire economy is
								built on exports. From agricultural products to clothing to electronics, the country has
								benefited greatly from Western companies diversifying outside China.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<q>Apple is moving a big chunk of iPad, Macbook, and Airpods production to Vietnam.</q>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<p>Apple is not completely new to Vietnam either — the company already assembled smaller
								products like wired EarPods in the country. And according to a source quoted by <a
									href="https://asia.nikkei.com/Business/Technology/Vietnam-to-make-Apple-Watch-and-MacBook-for-first-time-ever"
									target="_blank">Nikkei</a>, Apple began assembling the AirPods in Vietnam in March
								2020. That was quickly followed by the higher-end <a
									href="https://www.androidauthority.com/apple-airpods-pro-2nd-generation-review-3217269/">AirPods
									Pro</a>. Now, Apple is moving a significant percentage of iPad, MacBook, and Apple
								Watch production to Vietnam too.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<p>The Cupertino giant plans to achieve these goals through its manufacturing partners
								Foxconn, Pegatron, and Wistron. According to local <a
									href="https://thanhnien.vn/11-nha-may-trong-chuoi-cung-ung-apple-da-chuyen-sang-viet-nam-post1473060.html"
									target="_blank">news reports</a>, Apple had started assembly at 11 factories run by
								various manufacturing companies in Vietnam as of early 2022. Around that time, Foxconn
								also won a license from the Vietnamese government to build a 270 million assembly plant
								in the province of Bac Giang, less than 50 miles from the capital city of Hanoi. The
								facility will reportedly have enough capacity to ship eight million laptops and tablets
								per year.</p>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-d -_-A">
							<h3>Why is the iPhone now made in India?</h3>
						</div>
						<div class="-_-e">
							<div class="-_-Fk" style="max-width:1200px">
								<picture class="-_-6e" style="padding-top:66.67%;aspect-ratio:1200 / 800">
									<source sizes="(min-width: 64rem) 51.25rem, 80vw"
										srcSet="https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo.jpg.webp 1000w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-300x200.jpg.webp 300w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-768x512.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-840x560.jpg.webp 840w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-30x20.jpg.webp 30w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-16x11.jpg.webp 16w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-32x21.jpg.webp 32w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-28x19.jpg.webp 28w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-56x37.jpg.webp 56w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-64x43.jpg.webp 64w"
										type="image/webp" />
