d-view-ifixit-712w-400h.jpg.webp 712w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/iphone-exploded-view-ifixit-1000w-563h.jpg.webp 1000w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/iphone-exploded-view-ifixit-792w-446h.jpg.webp 792w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/iphone-exploded-view-ifixit-1280w-720h.jpg.webp 1280w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/iphone-exploded-view-ifixit-840w-472h.jpg.webp 840w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/iphone-exploded-view-ifixit-1340w-754h.jpg.webp 1340w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/iphone-exploded-view-ifixit-770w-433h.jpg.webp 770w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/iphone-exploded-view-ifixit-356w-200h.jpg.webp 356w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/iphone-exploded-view-ifixit-675w-380h.jpg.webp 675w","alt":"iphone exploded view ifixit","title":"iphone exploded view ifixit","caption":null,"credits":[{"title":"iFixit","pLink":null}],"size":{"w":1200,"h":675}}},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eWhile it’s tempting to take the \u003cem\u003eMade in China\u003c/em\u003e text on an iPhone at face value, not everything that goes into making an Apple product comes from one place.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"resource":"nc-multi","blocks":[{"postId":3234349,"resource":"nc-ad","id":"359091","type":"group","fallback":[]},{"postId":3234349,"resource":"nc-ad","id":"359154","type":"group","fallback":[]}],"visible":"mobile"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eThe iPhone’s display, for example, is made by either Samsung or LG in South Korea. The \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/what-is-flash-memory-3107166/\"\u003eflash memory\u003c/a\u003e and DRAM, on the other hand, likely come from Kioxia’s factories in Japan. And the Gorilla Glass that protects the screen could make its way from a Corning factory in the USA, Taiwan, or Japan. Apple\u0026#8217;s A-series \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/what-is-an-soc-smartphone-chipsets-explained-1051600/\"\u003eSoC\u003c/a\u003e, meanwhile, is custom silicon designed in California but manufactured by Taiwanese company TSMC. And we’ve barely even scratched the surface with this list so far.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"resource":"nc-ad-classed","className":"in-article-video","visible":"mobile","type":"video"},{"resource":"nc-ad-classed","className":"in-article","visible":"desktop","type":"plain"},{"resource":"nc-quote","html":"The iPhone relies on electronic components sourced from various countries, including the USA.","author":null},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\n\u003cp\u003eApple also relies on third parties for smaller, sometimes custom-made components like power management ICs, USB microcontrollers, wireless chipsets, and OLED drivers. These can be sourced from large companies such as Broadcom and Texas Instruments as well as smaller manufacturers in Southeast Asia. Elsewhere in the world, Apple has even \u003ca href=\"https://www.cnbc.com/2018/02/22/apples-potential-cobalt-mining-play-is-about-more-than-money-experts.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003etried to secure raw cobalt\u003c/a\u003e directly from miners to ensure that shortages don’t affect its ability to manufacture iPhone batteries.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eThe choice of supplier matters a great deal and it’s not just for quality control reasons either. Apple, alongside other Silicon Valley giants, has been accused of relying on child labor and \u003ca href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2019/dec/16/apple-and-google-named-in-us-lawsuit-over-congolese-child-cobalt-mining-deaths\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eunethical mining practices\u003c/a\u003e to cut costs. It goes without saying that such allegations could result in expensive lawsuits and negative publicity for the company.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"postId":3234349,"resource":"nc-ad","id":"newsletter-signup","type":"placement","fallback":[]},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003ch2\u003eFinal production: Where are iPhones made and assembled?\u003c/h2\u003e"},{"badges":[],"resource":"nc-img","image":{"src":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing.jpg","srcSet":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing.jpg 1920w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-300w-170h.jpg 300w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1200w-676h.jpg 1200w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-768w-432h.jpg 768w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1536w-865h.jpg 1536w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-16w-9h.jpg 16w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-32w-18h.jpg 32w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-28w-16h.jpg 28w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-56w-32h.jpg 56w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-64w-36h.jpg 64w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-712w-400h.jpg 712w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1000w-563h.jpg 1000w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-792w-446h.jpg 792w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1280w-720h.jpg 1280w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-840w-472h.jpg 840w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1340w-754h.jpg 1340w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-770w-433h.jpg 770w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-355w-200h.jpg 355w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-675w-380h.jpg 675w","webpSrcSet":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing.jpg.webp 1920w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-300w-170h.jpg.webp 300w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1200w-676h.jpg.webp 1200w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-768w-432h.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1536w-865h.jpg.webp 1536w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-16w-9h.jpg.webp 16w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-32w-18h.jpg.webp 32w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-28w-16h.jpg.webp 28w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-56w-32h.jpg.webp 56w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-64w-36h.jpg.webp 64w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-712w-400h.jpg.webp 712w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1000w-563h.jpg.webp 1000w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-792w-446h.jpg.webp 792w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1280w-720h.jpg.webp 1280w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-840w-472h.jpg.webp 840w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-1340w-754h.jpg.webp 1340w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-770w-433h.jpg.webp 770w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-355w-200h.jpg.webp 355w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/apple-iphone-14-plus-back-standing-675w-380h.jpg.webp 675w","alt":"apple iphone 14 plus back standing","title":"apple iphone 14 plus back standing","caption":null,"credits":[{"title":"Ryan Haines / Android Authority","pLink":null}],"size":{"w":1200,"h":675}}},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eWith singular components out of the way, who makes the iPhone before it reaches you? Factories in China once assembled every single iPhone, but that’s starting to change now.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"visible":"all","resource":"nc-ad-classed","className":"in-article","type":"plain"},{"resource":"nc-multi","blocks":[{"postId":3234349,"resource":"nc-ad","id":"api-in-article-ad","type":"placement","fallback":[]}],"visible":"all"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eStill, most factories dedicated to assembling the iPhone remain in China. The largest one, operated by manufacturing partner Foxconn, is located in Zhengzhou and employs over 300,000 workers. By many accounts, the complex \u003ca href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/29/technology/apple-iphone-china-foxconn.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eresembles a mini city\u003c/a\u003e more than a typical industrial site. That’s not surprising given that Foxconn reportedly assembles over half a million iPhones in a single day here. But that may not last forever as Apple looks to move some production to neighboring countries like India and Vietnam.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"resource":"nc-quote","html":"Apple has diversified its iPhone production outside China of late, with India and Vietnam emerging as top choices.","author":null},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\n\u003cp\u003eApple isn\u0026#8217;t the only consumer electronics company that has diversified outside China of late. Samsung and Xiaomi have found great success in other Asian countries too. The \u003ca href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/China_Plus_One\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eChina Plus One\u003c/a\u003e strategy has become a popular business strategy as companies look to achieve lower operating costs and lower their reliance on a single region.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eBoth Asian countries offer benefits to foreign investors looking to set up manufacturing facilities. They also offer geopolitical and economic stability — factors that severely affected Apple’s iPhone production in China. These bottlenecks even forced the company to put out a \u003ca href=\"https://www.apple.com/newsroom/2022/11/update-on-supply-of-iphone-14-pro-and-iphone-14-pro-max/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003epress release\u003c/a\u003e warning of longer wait times for deliveries.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"visible":"all","resource":"nc-ad-classed","className":"in-article-related","type":"plain"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003ch3\u003eWhy does Apple assemble products in Vietnam?\u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eVietnam is strategically located for global shipping — the country is in close geographic proximity to Apple’s existing \u003ca href=\"https://www.apple.com/supplier-responsibility/pdf/Apple-FY21-Supplier-List.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esupply chain footholds\u003c/a\u003e such as China, Taiwan, Japan, and others. It also has free trade agreements with other East Asian countries and is a member of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN). Finally, Vietnam’s entire economy is built on exports. From agricultural products to clothing to electronics, the country has benefited greatly from Western companies diversifying outside China.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"resource":"nc-quote","html":"Apple is moving a big chunk of iPad, Macbook, and Airpods production to Vietnam.","author":null},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\n\u003cp\u003eApple is not completely new to Vietnam either — the company already assembled smaller products like wired EarPods in the country. And according to a source quoted by \u003ca href=\"https://asia.nikkei.com/Business/Technology/Vietnam-to-make-Apple-Watch-and-MacBook-for-first-time-ever\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eNikkei\u003c/a\u003e, Apple began assembling the AirPods in Vietnam in March 2020. That was quickly followed by the higher-end \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/apple-airpods-pro-2nd-generation-review-3217269/\"\u003eAirPods Pro\u003c/a\u003e. Now, Apple is moving a significant percentage of iPad, MacBook, and Apple Watch production to Vietnam too.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eThe Cupertino giant plans to achieve these goals through its manufacturing partners Foxconn, Pegatron, and Wistron. According to local \u003ca href=\"https://thanhnien.vn/11-nha-may-trong-chuoi-cung-ung-apple-da-chuyen-sang-viet-nam-post1473060.html\" target=\"_blank\"\u003enews reports\u003c/a\u003e, Apple had started assembly at 11 factories run by various manufacturing companies in Vietnam as of early 2022. Around that time, Foxconn also won a license from the Vietnamese government to build a 270 million assembly plant in the province of Bac Giang, less than 50 miles from the capital city of Hanoi. The facility will reportedly have enough capacity to ship eight million laptops and tablets per year.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003ch3\u003eWhy is the iPhone now made in India?\u003c/h3\u003e"},{"badges":[],"resource":"nc-img","image":{"src":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo.jpg","srcSet":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo.jpg 1000w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-300x200.jpg 300w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-768x512.jpg 768w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-840x560.jpg 840w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-30x20.jpg 30w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-16x11.jpg 16w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-32x21.jpg 32w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-28x19.jpg 28w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-56x37.jpg 56w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-64x43.jpg 64w","webpSrcSet":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo.jpg.webp 1000w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-300x200.jpg.webp 300w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-768x512.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-840x560.jpg.webp 840w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-30x20.jpg.webp 30w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-16x11.jpg.webp 16w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-32x21.jpg.webp 32w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-28x19.jpg.webp 28w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-56x37.jpg.webp 56w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/Foxconn-logo-64x43.jpg.webp 64w","alt":"Foxconn logo","title":"Foxconn logo","caption":null,"credits":[],"size":{"w":1200,"h":800}}},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eIndia, Apple’s second favored manufacturing destination, offers strong incentives for local manufacturing compared to many of its neighbors. The government’s \u003cem\u003eMake in India\u003c/em\u003e initiative has been a runaway success. In 2020, it launched a 6 billion production-linked incentive scheme that rewards brands for setting up domestic manufacturing of smartphones and electronic components.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"visible":"all","resource":"nc-ad-classed","className":"in-article","type":"plain"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eAndroid brands like \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/xiaomi-1158659/\"\u003eXiaomi\u003c/a\u003e, Oppo, and Samsung have already joined the Make in India initiative through a combination of in-house and third-party manufacturing facilities. Some examples of the latter include Bharat FIH and Dixon Technologies, which assemble Xiaomi and Samsung smartphones.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eGiven these success stories, it’s no surprise that Apple aims to follow suit. It also helps that its biggest partner, Foxconn, already has a strong presence in India. The aforementioned Bharat FIH is a subsidiary of Foxconn Technology Group.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"resource":"nc-quote","html":"The Indian government offers smartphone makers various financial incentives to set up domestic factories.","author":null},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\n\u003cp\u003eApple’s decision to move its assembly lines to India could also increase the iPhone’s market share in the region. Currently, India levies a 22% customs duty on imported smartphones. This makes the iPhone significantly more expensive in the country than in most Western markets.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"visible":"all","resource":"nc-ad-classed","className":"in-article","type":"plain"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eWith local production, however, Apple can sidestep these high import fees and could pass on the savings to consumers. In fact, the company has already followed this strategy with previous-generation iPhone models, which it already assembles in the country. Even though the latest iPhone sells at a significant price premium in India, older models often get deep discounts — likely due to the aforementioned tax breaks.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"resource":"nc-quote","html":"By assembling the iPhone in India, Apple can sidestep high import fees and build domestic market share.","author":null},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\n\u003cp\u003eWith the iPhone 14, Apple began assembling current-generation iPhone models in India for the first time. The company tapped Foxconn for the job, specifically the latter’s Sriperumbudur factory in the state of Tamil Nadu. However, Apple only opted to move a small percentage of its iPhone 14 production from China to India — an estimated 5% right after launch.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003ch2\u003eWho will make Apple products like the iPhone in the future?\u003c/h2\u003e"},{"badges":[],"resource":"nc-img","image":{"src":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple.jpg","srcSet":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple.jpg 1920w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-300w-170h.jpg 300w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1200w-675h.jpg 1200w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-768w-432h.jpg 768w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1536w-864h.jpg 1536w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-16w-9h.jpg 16w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-32w-18h.jpg 32w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-28w-16h.jpg 28w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-56w-32h.jpg 56w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-64w-36h.jpg 64w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-712w-400h.jpg 712w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1000w-563h.jpg 1000w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-792w-446h.jpg 792w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1280w-720h.jpg 1280w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-840w-472h.jpg 840w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1340w-754h.jpg 1340w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-770w-433h.jpg 770w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-356w-200h.jpg 356w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-675w-380h.jpg 675w","webpSrcSet":"https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple.jpg.webp 1920w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-300w-170h.jpg.webp 300w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1200w-675h.jpg.webp 1200w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-768w-432h.jpg.webp 768w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1536w-864h.jpg.webp 1536w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-16w-9h.jpg.webp 16w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-32w-18h.jpg.webp 32w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-28w-16h.jpg.webp 28w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-56w-32h.jpg.webp 56w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-64w-36h.jpg.webp 64w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-712w-400h.jpg.webp 712w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1000w-563h.jpg.webp 1000w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-792w-446h.jpg.webp 792w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1280w-720h.jpg.webp 1280w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-840w-472h.jpg.webp 840w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-1340w-754h.jpg.webp 1340w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-770w-433h.jpg.webp 770w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-356w-200h.jpg.webp 356w, https://www.androidauthority.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Apple-logo-purple-675w-380h.jpg.webp 675w","alt":"Apple logo purple","title":"Apple logo purple","caption":null,"credits":[{"title":"Robert Triggs / Android Authority","pLink":null}],"size":{"w":1200,"h":675}}},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eEven with Apple’s migration to South and East Asia, the bulk of the company’s production facilities will remain in China. Several key electronic components are still sourced from the region. Moreover, China still has a great deal of manufacturing infrastructure already in place. However, the country\u0026#8217;s dominance will likely shrink over time. Still, Apple\u0026#8217;s existing factory partners stand to benefit either way as they will continue to build and operate facilities even outside China.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"visible":"all","resource":"nc-ad-classed","className":"in-article","type":"plain"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eWe’ve already discussed why Apple may want to shift assembly to Vietnam and India in the coming years. Financial forecasts expect the transition to happen sooner rather than later. A JPMorgan analyst \u003ca href=\"https://www.investing.com/news/stock-market-news/apple-is-more-aggressively-relocating-production-from-china-to-india-and-vietnam--jpm-432SI-2896365\" target=\"_blank\"\u003esaid\u003c/a\u003e the following in a note to the company\u0026#8217;s clients:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cblockquote\u003e\u003cdiv\u003eVietnam is emerging as the production hub for components (camera modules) and EMS of smaller-volume products (Apple Watch, Mac, iPads) and is already a major destination for AirPods manufacturing. For iPhone EMS, India appears to be the location of choice for diversifying the supply chain away from China.\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/blockquote\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe analyst further estimated that Apple will relocate around 25% of its iPhone production to India and 65% of AirPods assembly to Vietnam by 2025. Other products that could also see some assembly move away from China include the iPad, MacBook, and Apple Watch.\u003c/p\u003e"},{"resource":"nc-string","html":"\u003cp\u003eTo conclude, there’s no single answer as to where the iPhone gets made. While final assembly only takes place in two or three countries, the iPhone\u0026#8217;s individual components and raw materials come from nearly every corner of the world.\u003c/p\u003e\n"},{"resource":"nc-feedback","question":"Was this page helpful?","positive":{"msg":"Thanks for the feedback!","blocks":[{"resource":"nc-newsletter","done":{"title":"Thanks for subscribing!","goHomeLabel":"Take me home","image":null},"form":{"title":"The only tech newsletter you need.","text":"Join thousands of subscribers and receive a daily newsletter with the most critical headlines.","emailLabel":"email address","submitLabel":"Subscribe","policyHtml":"\u003cp\u003eBy signing up, you agree to our \u003ca href=\"/privacy-policy\"\u003ePrivacy Policy\u003c/a\u003e and European users agree 